node.title: New Covid-19 cases recorded in Samoa
node.description: Ten new cases of Covid-19 have been confirmed in Samoa among passengers who arrived into the country from Australia yesterday.
node.content:
["Ten new cases of Covid-19 have been confirmed in Samoa among passengers who arrived into the country from Australia yesterday.", "", "
Samoa Health Director Leausa Dr Take Naseri Photo: Samoa govt
", "Samoa's Director General of Health Dr Take Naseri confirmed the cases, which include an 11 month old baby, during a press conference this afternoon in Apia.", "The passengers were on a flight from Brisbane carrying 73 people.", "All are fully vaccinated and had tested negative for Covid-19 before departure.", "Dr Take Naseri said all of the passengers who tested positive since arriving in Samoa have been put into isolation and all are asymptomatic.", "Take Naseri said test samples will be sent to New Zealand on the first available flight to determine which variant of Covid-19 they are dealing with.", "But he said given the situation in Australia they suspect it is the Omicron variant.", "Meanwhile, the chairman of the National Emergency Operation Centre, Agafili Shem Leo, has urged those who have tested positive not to panic and to heed all conditions of their isolation.", "Agafili said they are hoping there has been no community transmission but they are prepared to quickly move up alert levels if need be."]
